FLOW
space_units                meters                    
time_units                 seconds                          
constant_flow              0.001    0.0      
!!!read_velocity              Case2D-AGUb        singlecolumn
END

POROSITY
!!!fix_porosity       0.077 
!!!fix_microporosity  0.0815
fix_porosity       0.99
fix_microporosity  0.0001
UpdateDDL          false
END

Condition FractureInlet
temperature        25.0
units              mol/kg 
Tracer             0.1
An-                0.000001
Cat+               0.000001
set_porosity       0.99 
set_microporosity  0.001
END


Condition Solid2
temperature        25.0
units              mol/kg 
Tracer             1.0E-08
An-                1.0E-30
Cat+               1.0E-30
set_porosity       0.99 
set_microporosity  0.001
END

!!!  **********************************************
!! Bogusite has 50 cm3/mol and a molar mass of 1000 g/mol
!! i.e. 20 000 g/dm3 bog 
!! with 0.05 volume fraction --> 1000 g/dm3
!! we want 1e5 m2 per dm3 --> 100 m2/g
!! if we want -1e-6 molc/m2 --> 5e-5 molc/g
!!! ***********************************************

!!!  ***************************
!!! For illite
!!!   SSA = 100 m2/g
!!!   Surface charge = 0.15-0.2 C m-2 that corresponds roughly to a CEC of 0.2 mol / kg illite
!!!   For illite/smectite, first approach is to consider a mix of the two phases even if it is an incorrect description on a mineralogical point of view.
!!!   Then lump together the CEC values as a function of total illite vs. smectite content. Total illite = illite + illite from illite/smectite
!!!   You can then pick the adsorption parameters from Appelo et al., 2010. They are for Opalinus Clay but they should be fine as a first try. Try to start with a Ca dominated surface.
!!!  ***************************

TRANSPORT
distance_units           meters
time_units               second
fix_diffusion            1.0e-29 

D_25    Tracer  1.0E-29
D_25  An-       1.0e-29
D_25  Cat+      1.0e-29 

D_MP    Tracer  1.0E-29
D_MP  An-       1.0e-29
D_MP  Cat+      1.0e-29 

END


